The paper discusses the usage of [n,k] MDS codes in a switching environment, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also studies the algorithmic problem of maximizing the read rate, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the area of computer architecture (cs.AR) as it discusses the parallelization of packet I/Os using multiple memory units.
